Control Flow

if/else
if works as both a statement and an expression:
// Statement form
if x &gt; 0 {
    print("positive");
} else {
    print("non-positive");
}

// Expression form — both branches must return compatible types
let abs_x = if x &gt;= 0 { x } else { -x };
Note: no parentheses around the condition. Braces are always required.


while loops
let mut sum = 0;
let mut i = 1;
while i &lt;= 100 {
    sum = sum + i;
    i = i + 1;
}


for loops
for iterates over ranges using start..end (exclusive upper bound):
let mut total = 0;
for i in 1..11 {
    total = total + i;
}


break and continue
Both work inside while and for loops:
for i in 0..10 {
    if i == 4 { break; }
    print(i);
}

let mut i = 0;
while i &lt; 5 {
    i = i + 1;
    if i == 3 { continue; }
    print(i);
}



Pattern Matching
