Gradient Descent and Automatic Differentiation
A simple but complete optimization loop — gradient descent on f(x) = (x - 3)^2:

Manual gradient descent converging to x = 3.0

fn f(x: f64) -&gt; f64 {
    (x - 3.0) * (x - 3.0)
}

fn grad_f(x: f64) -&gt; f64 {
    2.0 * (x - 3.0)
}

let x = 0.0;
let lr = 0.1;
let i = 0;

while i &lt; 100 {
    let g = grad_f(x);
    x = x - lr * g;
    i = i + 1;
}

print("Final x:", x);          // ~3.0
assert(abs(x - 3.0) &lt; 0.001);
For more complex cases, CJC-Lang has a full automatic differentiation engine — forward-mode via dual numbers and reverse-mode via tape-based gradient computation.


